<exercise label="chkpts-visualizing-solns">
	
	<introduction>
		<p>
			Answer the following questions using the <xref ref="family-of-solutions-figure-1" text="custom">interactive figure</xref> and the fact that <m>\ds y = ce^{x^2} + 3</m> is the general solution to the differential equation
		</p>
		<men xml:id="visual-de"> \ds \frac{dy}{dx} = 2xy - 6x. </men>
	</introduction>
	
	<task label="chkpt-visualizing-solns-1"><title> <em>Select-the-Best-Answer</em> </title>
		<statement>
			<p>
				Use the figure to determine the particular solution of <m>y = ce^{x^2} + 3</m> that passes through the point <m>(0,5)</m>?
			</p>
		</statement>
		<choices>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad\ds y = -2e^{x^2}+3</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. The value of <m>c</m> must make the solution pass through <m>(0, 5)</m>. Hover over the curve in the figure that passes through <m>(0,5)</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad\ds y = 0.5e^{x^2}+3</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. Remember that at <m>x = 0</m>, the exponential term <m>e^{x^2}</m> equals 1, so <m>y(0) = c + 3</m>. What value of <m>c</m> gives <m>y(0) = 5</m>? Hover over the curve in the figure that passes through <m>(0,5)</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice correct="yes">
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad\ds y = 2e^{x^2}+3</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Correct! The value <m>c = 2</m> ensures that <m>y(0) = 2 + 3 = 5</m>, so this solution passes through <m>(0, 5)</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad\ds y = 5e^{x^2}+3</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. The general solution would pass through <m>(0, 4)</m> if <m>c = 1</m>. Hover over the curve in the figure that passes through <m>(0,5)</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
		</choices>
	</task>

	<task label="chkpt-visualizing-solns-2"><title> <em>Select-the-Best-Answer</em> </title>
		<statement>
			<p>
				What is the value of <m>c</m> for the particular solution of <m>y = ce^{x^2} + 3</m> that passes through the point <m>(1,1)</m>?
			</p>
		</statement>
		<choices>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad c = -2</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. Hover over the curve in the figure that passes through <m>(1,1)</m> and look at the coefficient on <m>e^{x^2}</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad c = 0.5</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. Hover over the curve in the figure that passes through <m>(1,1)</m> and look at the coefficient on <m>e^{x^2}</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad c = 2</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. Hover over the curve in the figure that passes through <m>(1,1)</m> and look at the coefficient on <m>e^{x^2}</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice correct="yes">
				<statement>
					<p>
						<m>\quad c = -1</m>
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Correct! Hovering over the curve passing through <m>(1,1)</m> shows the particular solution <m>\ds y = -e^{x^2}+3</m>, so <m>c=1</m>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
		</choices>
	</task>

	<task label="chkpt-visualizing-solns-3"><title> <em>Select-the-Best-Answer</em> </title>
		<statement>
			<p>
				Which statement best describes the visual representation of a family of solutions?
			</p>
		</statement>
		<choices>
			<choice correct="yes">
				<statement>
					<p>
						Collection of all the possible solution curves.
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Correct! A family of solutions includes all possible solutions so visually it would be the collection of all solution curves.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						A single solution curve.
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. A family of solutions includes all possible particular solutions, not just one.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						The intersection of all the possible solution curves.
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. A family of solutions includes all possible solutions, not just their intersections.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						The curve of the general solution.
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					<p>
						Incorrect. The general solution is a framework for all possible solutions, but it is not the family of solutions itself. Also, since a general solution includes constants, doesn't have <q>a curve</q>.
					</p>
				</feedback>
			</choice>
		</choices>
	</task>
	
	<task label="chkpt-visualizing-solns-4"><title> <em>True-or-False</em> </title>
		<statement>
			<p>
				If <m>c = -1</m>, then the solution <m>y = ce^{x^2} + 3</m> passes through the origin <m>(0, 0)</m>.
			</p>
		</statement>
		<choices>
			<choice>
				<statement>
					<p>
						True
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					Incorrect. Try recalculating <m>y(0)</m> when <m>c = -1</m>. Which point does it pass through on the <m>y</m>-axis?
				</feedback>
			</choice>
			<choice correct="yes">
				<statement>
					<p>
						False
					</p>
				</statement>
				<feedback>
					Correct. If <m>c = -1</m>, then <m>y(0) = -1 + 3 = 2</m>, which passes through <m>(0,2)</m>.
				</feedback>
			</choice>
		</choices>
	</task>
	
</exercise>